# Ignore-rect mask for math_showcase_smoke (NumOS SDL2 emulator visual test).
#
# Reason: the Math Showcase renders a curated case (1 + 2/3 + x^2) through the same
# accepted MathCanvas the firmware uses, with the cursor OFF — so the math layout is
# byte-stable within and across runs. The ONLY volatile region across separate
# launches is the StatusBar clock, identical to settings_smoke: the clock label is
# drawn by StatusBar::updateClock() from the real wall clock (time() -> localtime ->
# "%02d:%02d", src/ui/StatusBar.cpp), so HH:MM reflects the minute each scripted run
# executes on. This is expected per-minute UI nondeterminism, NOT a renderer bug —
# the renderer geometry is frozen, so it is masked in the comparator, never edited.
#
# Region: same StatusBar clock as settings_smoke. The label is LV_ALIGN_LEFT_MID,6
# in lv_font_montserrat_12 (StatusBar.cpp:61-65), always 5 glyphs ("HH:MM"), box
# ~x[6..38] y[8..16]. A jitter diff across a minute rollover put the changed pixels
# at x[31..37] y[8..16] (minute-units digit); the HOUR digits can also change
# between arbitrary launches, so the mask covers the WHOLE label, not just minutes.
#
# Rect = full HH:MM label box (~x[6..38] y[8..16]) padded ~2px on each side ->
# x[4..40] y[6..18]. Tight to the clock: it does NOT cover the showcased math
# expression/fraction/superscript (rendered in the body, below the y=24 StatusBar
# separator), nor the centered title or the right-aligned battery/angle/modifier.
#
# x,y,w,h
4,6,37,13
